  "measurement_note": "Size is m, the number of operand tokens; each legal postfix stream has 2m-1 total tokens. Placing all operands before the additions produces a maximally skewed expression and grows the construction stack to m entries. The Accepted end-of-list stack and an independent iterative node stack take O(m) time. A correct recursive parser that repeatedly scans and slices each remaining postfix subtree takes O(m^2), completes all legal 5/20/50 tiers, and is rejected only by scaling.",
